                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-183-off983 t18280410-183-victim1055"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN CARGILL. I am a <rs id="t18280410-183-viclabel985" type="occupation">mariner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-183-victim1055 t18280410-183-viclabel985"></join>, and belong to the True<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182804100094"></xptr>which lay off Hermitage-stairs; the prisoner was engaged on board that vessel. On the 28th of February, I sent him on shore with my things to wash; he did not return - I went down and missed my watch from a drawer in my cabin; I had put it there about eight o'clock that morning; he was found at the Crooked Billet, public-house, with two women.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-183-person1056">
                  GEORGE 
                  DEVERELL
               <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1056" type="surname" value="DEVERELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1056" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1056" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took him in charge. I heard two women had been with him at the Crooked Billet - I went there and took them; the duplicate of the watch was found there, under the seat where he had been sitting.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-183-person1057">
                  ROBERT 
                  LINWOOD
               <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1057" type="surname" value="LINWOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1057" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-183-person1057" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live in Ratcliff-highway; the prisoner pawned this watch, on the 28th of February.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met a young man, and we went to have some beer. I heard the Theatre had fallen down. went to look at it; then went to another house, and was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280410-183-verdict986" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280410-183-verdict986" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
